<DOC><DOCNO> AP880330-0234 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-30-88 2227EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Britain-Drugs     03-30 0173</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Britain-Drugs,0177</SECOND><HEAD>Big Drug Hauls By British Customs</HEAD><DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Customs authorities said they seized 198 pounds ofColombian cocaine with a street value of about $22 millionWednesday and arrested two men.   A Customs and Excise spokesman, who under British practicerefused to be identified, said it was the second largest haul ofcocaine in Britain.   Earlier, Customs said it seized two tons of marijuana, worthabout $5.6 million, at Tilbury docks in east London from acontainer ship that came from Port Harcourt, Nigeria.   Six men and a woman were charged Wednesday with smuggling themarijuana, which Customs said was hidden in a cargo of compressedrubber bales. Initial discoveries of the cache were made more thantwo weeks ago.   Customs agents from London's Heathrow Airport made the cocainehaul but officials refused to give details except to say the twoarrests were in Surrey, a county neighboring London.   Last November, Customs found 457 pounds of cocaine worth about$90 million in a container on a ship at Southampton.</TEXT></DOC>